rComments: Easily my favorite prof. She's SO nice and super helpful - she goes out of her way to help students. She's very informal and treats you like a friend, not like a child like some profs. Overall, this class takes a lot of work, but it's not hard if you are a hard worker and you like the material. Very rewarding class - you come out with great skills.
A LOT OF WORK! EXTREMELY TIME CONSUMING!!! also she's a hard marker... online certificate you  must give it 100% or else you'll be screwed for the entire semester

A great prof!  I disagree with some of the below comments.  Koreen DOES try to engage class discussion - at least in the session I took - but none of my classmates would reply to her attempts so she gave up.  I do find it difficult to learn from her slides (using her slides alone) but if you listen to waht she is saying, it all makes perfect sense!

She talks fast and uses too many slides in her presentations. Does not engage class discussions and seems rushed through the course.   However, she is the best GIS person at U of O, very knowledgeable and cute to boot ;)

She tries to give personal attention to everyone - something i have never seen before with other profs.  You have to do actual work in class but you get used to it and in the end you end up with some real skills! Recommendation: pay attention to the lectures and take the the online certificate seriously!
Awesome, my favourite professor by far! Reccomend this course 1000 times over!

This class is like no other I've taken.  I love the hands-on experience and we are expected to think for ourselves and produce unique work.  She doesn't spell everything out for us or hold our hands which can be difficult some times but overall rewarding!
She's nice but her expectations (for the group project especially) aren't clear! Rubrics would help. Over all pretty good though.
Really helful, quick to reply to e-mails. Assessments were fair. I liked her a lot as a prof!
Very knowledgeable in her field.  A pleasure to listen to.
She is a nice person. But the workload is a little bit heavy.

This teacher is awesome, nice, sexiest teacher ever. very helpful and dedicated to her students. You wont regret it if you take course with her.The only thing is just the wording is sometimes confusing in her labs but everything is alright.
